sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant FE as Terraform Panel
    participant MCP as MCP Backend
    participant EXEC as Execution Service
    participant AWS as AWS Cloud

    User->>FE: 1. Enter description, click Plan
    FE->>MCP: 2. tools/call: run_terraform_plan_mcp (HCL)
    MCP->>EXEC: 3. create execution_id, write main.tf
    Note over EXEC: 4. terraform init -backend=false<br/>terraform plan -out=tfplan
    EXEC-->>MCP: 5. plan output + binary tfplan saved to workdir
    MCP->>MCP: 6. LLM summarises plan (plain English)
    MCP-->>FE: 7. plan summary + raw terraform output
    FE-->>User: 8. Show plan preview + Approve / Reject buttons

    Note over User,FE: --- Human approval gate ---

    User->>FE: 9. Click Approve
    FE->>MCP: 10. tools/call: run_terraform_apply_mcp (approved=true)
    MCP->>EXEC: 11. terraform apply tfplan -auto-approve
    EXEC->>AWS: 12. Infrastructure changes applied
    AWS-->>EXEC: 13. apply success + resource IDs
    EXEC-->>MCP: 14. apply output + SSH keys (if EC2 created)
    Note over EXEC: log to execution_log.json
    MCP-->>FE: 15. Apply successful + download links
    FE-->>User: 16. Confirm success, show Rollback button
